         <abstract>
            <p>This paper reports on computational experience with algorithms due to Loeb and Appel for rational approximation on discrete point sets. Following a brief review of the linear discrete approximation problem, the two rational algorithms are stated in a general setting. Finally, several numerical examples of applications to l&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;, l&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;, and l&lt;sub&gt;âˆž&lt;/sub&gt; approximation are supplied and discussed.</p>
          </abstract>
